us.phonetic: /v. prəˈdus, -ˈdjus; n. ˈprɑdus, -jus, ˈproʊdus, -djus/, (v. prə do̅o̅s′, -dyo̅o̅s′; n. prod′o̅o̅s, -yo̅o̅s, prō′do̅o̅s, -dyo̅o̅s)

example.eg: The bad policy produced many problems for the government.
example.egtrans: 这一糟糕的政策给政府带来了很多问题。

trans_examp.trans_cn: 导致, 引起, 带来

example.eg: This land produces a ton of corn for every hectare.
example.egtrans: 这块土地每公顷出产一吨玉米。

example.eg: After making a fortune as an actor, he then started producing movies.
example.egtrans: 他在当演员挣了大钱后，开始制作电影。

example.eg: How many Beatles albums were produced by George Martin?
example.egtrans: 披头士有多少专辑是乔治·马丁监制的？

example.eg: He produced his passport for inspection.
The produce is cheaper at the Korean market, especially the avocados.
example.egtrans: 农产品在朝鲜市场更便宜，尤其是鳄梨。

example.eg: The produce from that factory is excellent.
example.egtrans: 那家工厂的产品非常出色。
